[2] Response
- Sat 30 Nov 2019. North Kivu (Beni): MSF support
[Radio Moto; in French, machine trans., edited]
http://www.radiomoto.net/2019/11/30/lutte-contre-ebola-a-beni-msf-renouvelle-son-engagement-a-accompagner-la-population/
[Byline: Patrick Kalungwana]

Ebola fight in Beni: MSF renews its commitment to support the population

The NGO Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) is responding to the threats that Ebola response teams are facing these days. The organization advocates for the safety of healthcare workers so that they can effectively contribute to the Ebola response and the care of several other patients in the framework of free health care.

MSF remains in Beni at the request of the population. Regardless of ADF [Allied Democratic Forces] threats, it remains active. Despite the departure of other NGOs, this organization is resisting.

"MSF is still in Beni. I think the people of Beni still need it. And are still in contact with this population because if MSF is there it is to support the population of Beni by offering care ... We felt it was important that we still stay in Beni to support this population in distress," stated the MSF coordinator in Beni city.

MSF also promises to strengthen donations of medicines that can treat the wounded in 6 health centers and carry out other actions of Beni's general reference hospital.

"In Beni we support some health centers where people can access quality primary health care in free of charge. This is the 1st activity we have in Beni. Apart from that, our teams promise to strengthen the response to the care of the wounded, if necessary. And for preventive measures, MSF is preparing a donation of wound dressing kits to at least 6 health centers, while working with Beni General Hospital," said Pamphyle Bashimbe.

